3.1 Simple Linear Regression : feature가 1개¶

$Y = \beta_0 + \beta_1X$

  • $Y$ : response/output/target
  • $X$ : feature/input/predictor
  • $\beta_0$ is the intercept
  • $\beta_1$ is the coefficient for $X$

Response(Y) sales, 1 feature(X) TV ,

$sales = \beta_0 + \beta_1TV$

  • $\beta_0$ $\beta_1$ model coefficients ( weight)
  • simple linear regression : sales TV (RSS ) $\beta_0$ $\beta_1$

# 1.  import :     import   

# 2. Model Instantiation: Ordinary Least Squares (ols)  linear regression  
#    -   DataFrame  

lm = smf.ols(formula='Sales ~ TV', data=advertising)   

# 'advertising' DataFrame 'Sales' column resonse, 'TV' column feature 
#  linear regression   

# 3.   ,   ()  'lm_learned'  
lm_learned = lm.fit()

Multiple Linear Regression¶

multiple linear regression: feature response

$Y = \beta_0 + \beta_1X_1 + ... + \beta_nX_n$

Advertising TV, Radio, Newspaper feature , Sales response multiple linear regression :

$Sales = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \times TV + \beta_2 \times Radio + \beta_3 \times Newspaper$

In [24]:

Scikit-learn이 지원하는 머신러닝 알고리즘 및 적합한 알고리즘 선택 요령¶

scikit-learn Linear Regression¶

말 그대로 가장 밋밋한 Linear Regression 알고리즘인 Ordinary Least Squares Linear Regression 연습 - 3장의 Linear Regression 내용은 이것으로 다 됨¶

간략 scikit-learn 소개¶

  • () estimator . : an estimator is a Python object that implements the methods fit(X, y) and predict(T)

scikit-learn의 estimator들은 데이터에 대해 다음과 같은 조건을 요구함¶

  1. feature response
  2. feature response
  3. feature response NumPy ndarray DataFrame, Python array ndarray . , scipy sparse matrix .
  4. feature 2-D ndarray shape (n_samples, n_features) . Response 'n_samples' vector .

scikit-learn의 estimator 사용 패턴¶

1. estimator를 import¶

  • from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression

2. instantiate the estimator¶

  • model = LinearRegression() : instantiate estimator hyperparameter

3. estimator에게 데이터(X:feature, y:response)를 제공해 학습시킴 (모델 traing/fit¶

  • model.fit(X, y) : fit in-place , model

4. 학습된 estimator에 새로운 데이터의 feature(X_new)를 주고 response를 추정¶

  • y_predict = model.predict(X_new)

추천¶

predict()에 feature array를 줄 때 가능한 DataFrame으로 주자. DataFrame은 2D 데이터 구조이고, 보통 column name도 함께 쓰기에 에러도 준다.¶

In [111]:

X_new
